==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phlogopite
<hw>Phlog"o*pite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>flogwpo`s</grk> firelike.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A kind of
mica having generally a peculiar bronze-red or copperlike color and a
pearly luster. It is a silicate of aluminia, with magnesia, potash, and
some fluorine. It is characteristic of crystalline limestone or dolomite
and serpentine. See <er>Mica</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phlogosis</ent>⟦br⟧
